This paper deals with the problem of modeling and inference in dynamic systems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of continuous time Bayesian networks (CTBNs) and expectation-propagation (EP) inference algorithm also suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling and inference, which is a subfield of both AI and LG. The paper also discusses the use of a cluster graph architecture, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and network analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the application of this approach to modeling and inference in complex systems suggests a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
